<TITLE> Referee halts Espanyol-Barcelona game after crowd trouble </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MADRID, Sept 28 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Crowd trouble forced the Primera Liga match between Espanyol and Barcelona to be halted for several minutes during the second half on Saturday. Home side Espanyol were 1-0 in front when television pictures showed a flare being lobbed from the upper stand in the direction of the fans below, leading referee Medina Cantalejo to take the players off the pitch for almost 10 minutes. The game was eventually restarted
